item.title: Best laptop ever?
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

My PC (asus laptop) has a 1080p HD LCD, NVIDIA GTX440M Cuda * 1.5GB, a 750GB HDD (I also installed another 1TB HDD), i7 Quad-core. Subwoofer (small, but it is a subwoofer), THX trusound technology. Colorshing technology. I can order a 3D-ready monitor replacment for like $400 or something like that (don’t remember the price at all actually, thats pulling it outta my ass). For the price, its not a bad laptop, but it can get much better.

(yes I am going off of labels here) Got myn in January.
http://www.amazon.com/G73JW-A1-Republic-Gamers-17-3-Inch-Gaming/dp/B0041RRS0I

EDIT: LOL @ xryz - Didn’t realise you posted a link to the exact laptop I got.

item.title: Best laptop ever?
item.dc:creator: @xryz xryz
item.description:
@xryz wrote:

i would have to say thats a awesome price for a laptop with those specs(my laptop[toshiba satellite L505-ES5036 if it wasnt a gift i would of got something better for the same price.] was $100 more than this, only upside to mine is it has a 4" larger screen and twice the ram, but i would rather have a gfx card with 1gb dedicated ram and overclockable cpu). but not the best laptop. this one probably isnt the best:http://www.bestlaptopsdaily.com/asus-g73sw-xa1/ but i guarantee its better than my classmates alienware which he paid $4000 for…
